# Audit Logging Rules

- Log sensitive actions: auth changes, permission changes, pricing changes, inventory adjustments, order state changes, tenant lifecycle actions.
- Include actor, tenant, target entity, action, timestamp, and correlation/request IDs.
- Keep audit records append-only.
- Avoid logging secrets or raw payment credentials.
- Ensure audit queries remain feasible for investigations.
